-- Euro Strengthens as Spain Beats Maximum Target at Bill Auction
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   R e y n o l d s
-- 2012-04-17T08:48:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/euro-strengthens-as-spain-beats-maximum-target-at-bill-auction.html
The euro strengthened versus the
yen and the dollar after  Spain  sold more than its maximum target
at a bill auction.  The shared currency climbed 0.3 percent to 106.01 yen at
9:46 a.m. London time and advanced 0.1 percent to $1.3148.  Spain sold 3.18 billion euros of 12- and 18-month bills,
compared to a maximum target of 3 billion euros.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nicholas Reynolds at 
 nreynolds2@bloomberg.net  